  "text": "Neutrophil-to-lymphocyte (N/L) ratio is a new prognostic marker in patients with CAD undergoing coronary angiography, percutaneous coronary intervention, and coronary artery bypass grafting [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Recently, higher N/L ratio has been associated with increased risk for mortality in patients with acute decompensated HF [CITATION_3] . However, no data exist about the association between N/L ratio and response to CRT. We investigated the relationship between N/L ratio and response to CRT.",
